1
00:01:34,729 --> 00:01:37,539
[Bloom Life]

2
00:01:38,479 --> 00:01:42,620
[2007]

3
00:01:41,479 --> 00:01:43,759
Look, two flocks of pigeons are racing.

4
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,610
Look.

5
00:01:45,630 --> 00:01:47,430
Nur's flock is impressive!

6
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:49,180
Will his pigeons win?

7
00:01:49,539 --> 00:01:51,700
Sadiq's tumbler pigeons

8
00:01:51,729 --> 00:01:53,270
are even better.

9
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:55,400
Uncle Nur definitely won't win.

10
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,280
That pigeon is flying towards us!

11
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:01,580
What are you waiting for?
Let's go after it!

12
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:24,079
Pigeons know the way home.

13
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:28,530
Uncle.

14
00:02:30,370 --> 00:02:32,320
Grandma, Auntie.

15
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:33,180
Look,

16
00:02:33,180 --> 00:02:35,800
you scared the dewdrops off my roses.

17
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:38,610
Where are the dewdrops? Let me see.

18
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,060
We finally caught it.

19
00:02:56,770 --> 00:02:58,930
It's so cute, all white.

20
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:07,460
Arzugul.

21
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,210
Laili?

22
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:11,360
Come down.

23
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:15,200
This is the pigeon
that flew away from the flock?

24
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,360
You caught it?

25
00:03:27,050 --> 00:03:30,390
[Episode 6: The Home Won't Change]

26
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:46,740
Why did you also plant a tree here?

27
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:48,300
I just picked it up on the road.

28
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,820
It looked half-dead.

29
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:52,070
If I can save it, it's a life saved.

30
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,340
Be careful.

31
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:55,150
Planting a tree creates a bond.

32
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,720
You have to water and fertilize it.

33
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,780
I'm already running a homestay here.

34
00:03:58,870 --> 00:04:00,370
So I don't mind being "tied down" a bit.

35
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:01,830
Didn't you plant one, too?

36
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:05,630
This is my home.

37
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,500
What's wrong with me planting one here?

38
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:08,250
Besides,

39
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:09,910
I might not stay here forever.

40
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:12,550
Wait,

41
00:04:13,810 --> 00:04:15,310
you accepted my job offer,

42
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:17,160
you can't just leave anytime.

43
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:32,770
♪ My little sapling ♪

44
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:34,409
So ugly.

45
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:45,090
Laili.

46
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,010
Ayisha, Cai, you're here.

47
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,640
What do you want to eat today?

48
00:04:49,170 --> 00:04:49,909
What do you want to eat?

49
00:04:49,909 --> 00:04:53,090
-Fried chicken and yogurt.
-Fried chicken and yogurt.

50
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:54,440
Okay, take a seat first.

51
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:55,960
Let's go.

52
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,030
Later, when Laili

53
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:04,890
serves all our food,

54
00:05:04,890 --> 00:05:06,090
give her a heart sign

55
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:07,170
when you thank her.

56
00:05:17,070 --> 00:05:18,000
The food is here.

57
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:18,850
Let me help.

58
00:05:20,450 --> 00:05:23,550
-Thank you, Laili.
-Thank you, Laili.

59
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,750
Who taught you that?

60
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:27,630
We learned it ourselves.

61
00:05:27,630 --> 00:05:29,160
Yourselves? From whom?

62
00:05:36,860 --> 00:05:39,310
Is your instrument shop very free lately?

63
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:41,270
Why does someone run two blocks every day

64
00:05:41,270 --> 00:05:42,510
just to buy chicken wings?

65
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:43,400
No.

66
00:05:43,930 --> 00:05:44,790
It's these two.

67
00:05:45,070 --> 00:05:46,190
They said the food here is delicious

68
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:47,630
and begged me to bring them.

69
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:48,800
Right after lunch,

70
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,250
Brother brought us here

71
00:05:51,270 --> 00:05:52,530
to eat.

72
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,350
Brother burned the eggplants last night

73
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:56,240
and mentioned Laili—

74
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,390
Eat fried chicken.

75
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,120
Laili.

76
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:02,680
What's wrong?

77
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:06,780
This is for you.

78
00:06:06,970 --> 00:06:07,900
Burn ointment.

79
00:06:07,990 --> 00:06:10,650
-We kept an extra for roasting lamb.
-Thank you.

80
00:06:14,820 --> 00:06:15,560
Here.

81
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,040
When you apply it,

82
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,680
go clockwise.

83
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:41,710
You apply it for me.

84
00:06:55,350 --> 00:07:00,630
♪ Woods, oh poplar woods ♪

85
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:04,890
What's wrong? What happened?

86
00:07:04,890 --> 00:07:06,060
That was so loud.

87
00:07:06,340 --> 00:07:07,450
What's wrong? What's that sound?

88
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:08,250
What's wrong?

89
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,260
What happened?

90
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:14,280
Batur, what happened?

91
00:07:14,630 --> 00:07:15,490
The earth kiln.

92
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,160
Don't just stand there.

93
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:20,070
Throw water in it. Yes, throw it right in.

94
00:07:25,230 --> 00:07:26,760
I told you to watch the kiln.

95
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:28,980
Where on earth did you go?

96
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:29,680
I...

97
00:07:30,570 --> 00:07:31,680
Where did you go?

98
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:32,680
I thought

99
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,800
the temperature was stable,

100
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,000
so I went out for a bit.

101
00:07:36,190 --> 00:07:38,190
You can't leave the kiln
while it's firing.

102
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:40,060
Don't you know that?

103
00:07:40,980 --> 00:07:41,770
Ma'am.

104
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:44,690
I heard that other earthenware shops

105
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:45,360
installed electric kilns,

106
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,920
so I wanted to take a look.

107
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,680
Electric kilns fire fast and stably.

108
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,830
And people don't have to

109
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:52,159
watch them all the time.

110
00:07:52,570 --> 00:07:54,040
I even got the phone number

111
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,130
of the electric kiln manufacturer.

112
00:07:56,130 --> 00:07:56,930
Master, look.

113
00:07:57,130 --> 00:07:58,730
Here is their business card.

114
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,950
Master, electric kilns are really useful.

115
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:01,630
Master!

116
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:03,130
Since the kiln cracked,

117
00:08:03,130 --> 00:08:04,390
let's just replace it.

118
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:07,360
Batur.

119
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,510
Replace it?

120
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,750
Do you have any idea

121
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:15,390
just how important

122
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,660
this ancient earthen kiln is?

123
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,450
My great-grandfather

124
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:24,240
left it behind.

125
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,510
It's more precious to me than life itself.

126
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,750
You, kid,

127
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,010
are always looking for

128
00:08:30,410 --> 00:08:31,850
the easy way out.

129
00:08:32,650 --> 00:08:34,220
Haven't I told you

130
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,669
that our family

131
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,880
will never use those things?

132
00:08:38,169 --> 00:08:39,230
Do you understand?

133
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:43,650
Other earthenware shops

134
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:47,160
have more orders than they can handle.

135
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,340
We're stuck with this broken earth kiln.

136
00:08:51,370 --> 00:08:52,970
How can we compete with them?

137
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:15,840
Mom.

138
00:09:16,670 --> 00:09:18,670
How much does it cost to fix the kiln?

139
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:21,380
I've got 400 saved up here.

140
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:23,190
This is what's left from breakfast.

141
00:09:23,190 --> 00:09:24,560
-Mom, take it.
-No need.

142
00:09:24,790 --> 00:09:25,670
It will be fine.

143
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,200
Trust me. It's really fine.

144
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,320
I can get all the rest
of the money together.

145
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,790
Our kiln will be fixed.

146
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:32,640
I'll figure something out.

147
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:33,820
This...

148
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:27,770
Timur,

149
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:31,760
have you ever seen a merlin
with your own eyes?

150
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,960
They move so fast,

151
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:40,180
catching little birds like a bullet.

152
00:10:41,890 --> 00:10:44,100
Sometimes I wonder,

153
00:10:48,770 --> 00:10:49,750
if

154
00:10:50,330 --> 00:10:54,040
my son Asimjan were still alive,

155
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:57,460
would my daughter Laili

156
00:10:58,930 --> 00:11:03,660
still be as lively and active
as she is now,

157
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:07,100
with the passion of a merlin?

158
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:12,300
Maybe it's time to break the rule of passing it

159
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:14,650
only to sons.

160
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:30,150
Why can't you get the hang of it?

161
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:33,270
The spout must be made higher.

162
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:36,680
Otherwise, the water
will flow out with no pressure.

163
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:41,260
Why are you just standing there?

164
00:11:43,580 --> 00:11:44,180
Come here.

165
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:45,900
Come here.

166
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:54,840
Come on,

167
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:56,330
you try one.

168
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:01,180
Come on.

169
00:12:03,980 --> 00:12:04,530
Do it.

170
00:12:10,610 --> 00:12:11,600
Slow down.

171
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:14,410
Good.

172
00:12:14,830 --> 00:12:15,870
Very good.

173
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,470
Families making earthenware like ours

174
00:12:21,540 --> 00:12:24,540
would originally only
pass the craft to sons.

175
00:12:25,170 --> 00:12:25,940
But

176
00:12:26,180 --> 00:12:29,710
you've loved making earthenware
so much since you were little.

177
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,030
I have

178
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,790
seen it all.

179
00:12:33,610 --> 00:12:34,520
Nowadays,

180
00:12:35,180 --> 00:12:38,830
more and more families
use machines to make earthenware.

181
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,410
I want to teach you
the most traditional craft.

182
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,440
Things made by machines

183
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:48,660
are all the same

184
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:50,250
and boring.

185
00:12:50,480 --> 00:12:52,850
Only handmade earthenware

186
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,600
has warmth.

187
00:12:55,620 --> 00:12:57,250
I can't

188
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:02,610
fully convey to you what it feels like

189
00:13:04,080 --> 00:13:06,240
to touch the clay.

190
00:13:06,890 --> 00:13:09,290
It all depends on your own understanding

191
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:10,370
and effort.

192
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:17,050
The water inside...

193
00:13:17,760 --> 00:13:19,590
It's dry. Oh, good.

194
00:13:41,030 --> 00:13:41,660
Dad.

195
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,720
Dad.

196
00:13:46,630 --> 00:13:48,130
Why did you buy this?

197
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,610
How can a girl like a flower

198
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:53,140
have hands full of cracks?

199
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,970
Dad, let me help you.

200
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:56,610
No need.

201
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:57,150
Give it to me.

202
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:58,080
You go practice.

203
00:13:58,100 --> 00:13:59,160
And practice well,

204
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:00,240
okay?

205
00:14:19,260 --> 00:14:20,620
Thank you, Zhou.

206
00:14:21,050 --> 00:14:23,810
You got all these hard-to-find paints
for me.

207
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:25,390
You didn't have to deliver them in person.

208
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:27,990
It's fine, Auntie. I was afraid they
might get damaged in transit.

209
00:14:27,990 --> 00:14:28,990
Don't mention it.

210
00:14:29,130 --> 00:14:30,230
After all, Xia Zi

211
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,960
is my good friend.

212
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:35,720
Zhou.

213
00:14:35,740 --> 00:14:36,420
Yes, Auntie.

214
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:39,510
Let's not tell Xia Zi about this for now.

215
00:14:40,050 --> 00:14:42,310
I'm afraid she'll worry unnecessarily.

216
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,080
Don't worry, I won't tell her.

217
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:23,550
I'll sing a song I wrote myself.

218
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:25,740
It's my first time singing it.

219
00:15:26,870 --> 00:15:27,720
Good!

220
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:45,100
♪ The night sky tonight ♪

221
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:48,410
♪ Is filled with beautiful dreams ♪

222
00:15:48,980 --> 00:15:52,580
♪ In the grass of the valley ♪

223
00:15:52,610 --> 00:15:56,150
♪ Who hid away time and space ♪

224
00:15:56,420 --> 00:16:00,150
♪ Those long, lingering memories ♪

225
00:16:00,170 --> 00:16:03,940
♪ Are so captivating ♪

226
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:07,550
♪ Searching for the lost self ♪

227
00:16:07,650 --> 00:16:11,650
♪ What was it that you threw into time ♪

228
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:16,910
♪ What is it that can define you and me ♪

229
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:26,810
♪ Laili ♪

230
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:33,460
♪ Laili ♪

231
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,600
I didn't expect you
to write your own songs.

232
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:48,000
Music is all connected.

233
00:16:48,290 --> 00:16:51,240
And Grandpa also wants me
to learn more things.

234
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:54,620
Actually, I've always wanted
to compose my own music.

235
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:56,390
Actually, me too.

236
00:16:57,700 --> 00:17:01,030
I think besides those traditional jars,

237
00:17:01,030 --> 00:17:02,600
I also want to make some

238
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:03,840
different things,

239
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:07,030
like putting my feelings

240
00:17:07,180 --> 00:17:08,510
or my mood

241
00:17:08,510 --> 00:17:09,700
into the clay.

242
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:11,200
I think it would be different.

243
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,230
Definitely.

244
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:15,060
And I believe you can do it.

245
00:17:17,270 --> 00:17:18,569
Also, right now,

246
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:21,030
I have some motifs in my head.

247
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:24,750
A melody keeps playing in my mind.

248
00:17:24,950 --> 00:17:26,119
-Do you want to hear it?
-What melody?

249
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:27,020
Yes.

250
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:27,770
Then I'll play it for you.

251
00:17:27,770 --> 00:17:28,170
Okay.

252
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:49,860
What time is it?

253
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:51,020
Why are you singing?

254
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:53,400
Are you going to let people sleep or not?

255
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:07,480
You go first.

256
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:14,140
I actually have 2 pieces
of good news for you.

257
00:19:14,510 --> 00:19:15,240
Tell me.

258
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,690
The first bit of good news...

259
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,640
Is it that funny?

260
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:25,710
I'm telling you seriously.

261
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:27,350
The first bit of good news

262
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:30,550
is that my father finally
agreed to teach me earthenware.

263
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:31,910
That's great!

264
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:33,980
The second piece of good news is

265
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,000
that now that I'm learning
the earthenware,

266
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:39,200
I don't have to marry Mulading anymore.

267
00:19:43,210 --> 00:19:44,470
So you are off the hook.

268
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:58,880
But I don't want to be off the hook.

269
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:12,960
I like you.

270
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:17,170
I want to be your boyfriend.

271
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:18,810
This time, I mean it.

272
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:20,110
No more pretending.

273
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:25,500
But...

274
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:29,200
I'm not as pretty as Minawar.

275
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:31,840
And I'm not as smart as Arzugul.

276
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,050
I feel like I...

277
00:20:34,050 --> 00:20:35,430
Grandpa told me,

278
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,310
"Choose a lover with your heart,

279
00:20:38,590 --> 00:20:39,510
not your eyes."

280
00:20:40,590 --> 00:20:42,250
I just like you the way you are.

281
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,770
I like you, too.

282
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:50,330
What?

283
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,680
What did you just say?

284
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:54,090
I... I said I like you too.

285
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:54,890
Say it again.

286
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:56,750
Say it a bit louder.

287
00:20:56,750 --> 00:20:58,420
I said I like you too!

288
00:20:58,680 --> 00:20:59,610
What did you say?

289
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:00,500
I said—

290
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:02,010
You what?

291
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:03,480
What?

292
00:21:03,480 --> 00:21:05,200
She said she likes you, too!

293
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:07,410
♪ Girl, oh girl ♪

294
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:09,300
♪ Listen to a few words from me ♪

295
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,670
I like you.

296
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:11,900
♪ Could you please leave me ♪

297
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:13,800
♪ Your QQ number ♪

298
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:16,390
♪ If you are a big dinosaur ♪

299
00:21:16,410 --> 00:21:18,120
♪ I'll be a little frog too ♪

300
00:21:18,140 --> 00:21:20,800
♪ Let's not look down on each other ♪

301
00:21:20,830 --> 00:21:27,300
♪ Let's just be friends ♪

302
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:45,580
♪ Darling, come on, come on, come on ♪

303
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,420
Grandma went out in the afternoon.

304
00:22:21,420 --> 00:22:23,050
She hasn't come back yet.

305
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,290
Mom!

306
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:26,220
Mom!

307
00:22:26,220 --> 00:22:26,980
You look over there.

308
00:22:26,980 --> 00:22:28,040
I'll look this way.

309
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:31,050
Grandma!

310
00:22:33,240 --> 00:22:34,590
Grandma.

311
00:22:41,090 --> 00:22:41,960
Grandma.

312
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,410
Grandma.

313
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:50,550
Why are you here?

314
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:56,600
I'm here waiting
for your grandpa to come home.

315
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:58,580
Your grandpa

316
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:01,530
went to Yarkant to collect taxes.

317
00:23:02,090 --> 00:23:04,110
He was riding a horse,

318
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,370
carrying a hunting rifle.

319
00:23:07,780 --> 00:23:09,990
How handsome he was.

320
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:11,620
In a few days,

321
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:13,240
he will come back.

322
00:23:14,350 --> 00:23:15,660
I wonder if he returns,

323
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:18,660
will he be able to find our home?

324
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:24,070
Grandma.

325
00:23:24,810 --> 00:23:27,550
Our home is over there.

326
00:23:28,830 --> 00:23:29,850
No.

327
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,960
This is our house.

328
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:34,750
Look.

329
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:37,810
Isn't this pattern different from ours?

330
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:42,170
The color is the same,

331
00:23:42,250 --> 00:23:44,480
but the pattern has changed.

332
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,900
If my husband comes back,

333
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,090
can he find our home?

334
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:55,830
When your grandfather comes back,

335
00:23:55,860 --> 00:24:01,420
I'm worried he won't find his way home.

336
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:06,750
What if he can't find home?

337
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,650
Grandma's words

338
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:15,740
made me think about the direction
of the homestay renovation.

339
00:24:16,010 --> 00:24:17,410
The carvings on the gate,

340
00:24:18,210 --> 00:24:19,650
the smell of figs,

341
00:24:20,430 --> 00:24:21,890
and the touch of old things

342
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:25,100
all help a wandering little pigeon

343
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,030
recognize the way home.

344
00:25:53,330 --> 00:25:54,200
Hurry up.

345
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,530
The mooncakes are here.

346
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:58,670
Aunt Chang Yue bought these
especially for us.

347
00:25:58,670 --> 00:26:00,470
Come on, everyone, have a taste.

348
00:26:00,570 --> 00:26:01,620
Come on.

349
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:05,170
It's the Mid-Autumn Festival.
How can we not have mooncakes?

350
00:26:05,170 --> 00:26:05,950
Chang Yue.

351
00:26:06,390 --> 00:26:08,770
You haven't been
to our house for a long time.

352
00:26:08,770 --> 00:26:09,770
Come have a taste.

353
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:10,700
Mom.

354
00:26:11,250 --> 00:26:13,010
Aunt Jiang told you
to avoid "trigger" foods

355
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:14,410
and eat more vegetables.

356
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:15,640
It's a holiday today.

357
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:17,420
If Auntie wants to eat it,
let her have more.

358
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:18,530
Why are you giving her more?

359
00:26:18,530 --> 00:26:19,140
Don't listen to her.

360
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:20,200
Leave my mom alone.

361
00:26:20,460 --> 00:26:21,400
Come on.

362
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:22,140
Everyone, eat.

363
00:26:22,140 --> 00:26:23,470
Everyone, have a taste.

364
00:26:23,530 --> 00:26:24,260
You try some.

365
00:26:25,380 --> 00:26:26,600
Come on, eat.

366
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:27,480
Come on, everyone, eat.

367
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:28,740
Eat while it's hot.

368
00:26:29,700 --> 00:26:31,210
While everyone is gathered here,

369
00:26:31,210 --> 00:26:33,470
I have some good news to share.

370
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:38,010
Our old inn

371
00:26:38,010 --> 00:26:40,050
has been running for many years.

372
00:26:40,510 --> 00:26:42,680
I have spent most of my life here.

373
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:45,610
My great-great-grandfather

374
00:26:45,610 --> 00:26:47,270
was also born in this house.

375
00:26:47,270 --> 00:26:48,640
When my dad was young,

376
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:50,270
he renovated it

377
00:26:50,270 --> 00:26:51,660
a bit.

378
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:53,690
No one

379
00:26:54,330 --> 00:26:56,130
loves this place more than we do.

380
00:26:57,090 --> 00:26:58,170
As everyone knows,

381
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,050
our century-old house

382
00:27:00,070 --> 00:27:01,750
can't keep up
with the outside development now.

383
00:27:01,750 --> 00:27:03,150
If we just wait like this,

384
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:05,010
I'm afraid it

385
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,650
will be ruined in my hands.

386
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,520
It's so beautiful.

387
00:27:14,530 --> 00:27:15,720
So pretty.

388
00:27:15,940 --> 00:27:16,570
This is

389
00:27:16,590 --> 00:27:20,090
a gift from me to Grandma and everyone.

390
00:27:20,410 --> 00:27:22,070
The blueprint for the new inn.

391
00:27:22,310 --> 00:27:23,050
Come, let me see.

392
00:27:23,050 --> 00:27:23,510
Auntie.

393
00:27:24,420 --> 00:27:25,030
Look how nice the design is.

394
00:27:25,030 --> 00:27:26,090
It's so beautiful.

395
00:27:26,740 --> 00:27:28,610
Dad, our house is in there, too.

396
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:31,290
Why does this look so familiar to me?

397
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:34,110
This is a sketch
I've been working on lately.

398
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,790
I made some changes

399
00:27:35,790 --> 00:27:37,240
to the internal structure,

400
00:27:37,240 --> 00:27:38,770
but the exterior is essentially
a recreation

401
00:27:38,770 --> 00:27:40,680
of how it looked back in Grandpa's day.

402
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:41,740
That way,

403
00:27:41,740 --> 00:27:44,830
Grandpa will never
lose his way home again.

404
00:27:45,660 --> 00:27:46,590
Grandma.

405
00:27:47,110 --> 00:27:48,560
The home won't change.

406
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,020
Please don't worry.

407
00:27:51,450 --> 00:27:53,480
The home won't change.

408
00:27:54,030 --> 00:27:56,550
The home really won't change.

409
00:28:02,110 --> 00:28:03,310
Does Grandma like it?

410
00:28:03,410 --> 00:28:04,480
Yes.

411
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:06,530
She said, "The home won't change."

412
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:33,870
What are you doing

413
00:28:33,890 --> 00:28:35,000
sneaking around?

414
00:28:40,290 --> 00:28:42,020
Let me show you some good stuff.

415
00:28:44,650 --> 00:28:45,610
Hey.

416
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:48,440
Why did you withdraw so much money?

417
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:50,300
We're starting work soon, right?

418
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,090
What the workers care about most

419
00:28:52,090 --> 00:28:52,920
is this:

420
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:54,700
solid cash.

421
00:28:56,290 --> 00:28:58,820
I find you're becoming
more and more like a Kashgar local.

422
00:28:58,820 --> 00:29:00,680
Have you ever heard a saying here?

423
00:29:01,330 --> 00:29:02,610
How much do Kashgar people

424
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:04,400
love doing business?

425
00:29:04,420 --> 00:29:05,830
Even if there's only one person,

426
00:29:05,830 --> 00:29:08,760
they'd sell things from their left pocket
to their right pocket.

427
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,680
It's...

428
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:12,500
They don't care about the result,
but the process.

429
00:29:27,960 --> 00:29:29,900
As the inn's renovation begins,

430
00:29:30,530 --> 00:29:31,530
everyone's heart

431
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:33,140
flutters with it.

432
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:36,850
Amidst the reluctance,

433
00:29:37,030 --> 00:29:38,760
it is also full of expectation.

434
00:29:40,530 --> 00:29:41,270
This century-old house embedded in

435
00:29:41,270 --> 00:29:43,640
everyone's memory

436
00:29:45,590 --> 00:29:46,680
will also welcome

437
00:29:47,020 --> 00:29:48,760
its new life cycle.

438
00:30:30,380 --> 00:30:32,510
Forty days have passed
in the blink of an eye.

439
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:34,110
She grows so fast.

440
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:35,720
So beautiful. Looks exactly like you.

441
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,240
Really?

442
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,140
Yes.

443
00:30:39,440 --> 00:30:40,290
Come.

444
00:30:40,660 --> 00:30:41,850
Let Grandma hold you.

445
00:30:41,850 --> 00:30:42,900
Thanks for your hard work, child.

446
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:44,070
No, no.

447
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,840
Let Grandma hold you.

448
00:30:46,870 --> 00:30:48,190
Let me hold you.

449
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:50,240
Let me hold you.

450
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:53,570
Come.

451
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:56,790
Come.

452
00:30:57,170 --> 00:30:58,530
Use golden water

453
00:30:58,560 --> 00:31:00,830
to wash our baby's hands.

454
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:05,940
Little feet.

455
00:31:05,940 --> 00:31:07,320
Wash the little feet.

456
00:31:07,350 --> 00:31:08,680
Little feet. All right.

457
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,220
Come,

458
00:31:09,570 --> 00:31:11,070
Minawar,

459
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:11,720
look.

460
00:31:11,980 --> 00:31:15,740
This is a gift
for my eldest granddaughter.

461
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:18,640
About this...

462
00:31:20,220 --> 00:31:21,220
Next year,

463
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:24,010
when you give me a big,
healthy baby boy...

464
00:31:24,010 --> 00:31:25,140
I'll keep it for him.

465
00:31:29,550 --> 00:31:31,180
Let Auntie hold you.

466
00:31:31,790 --> 00:31:32,720
So cute.

467
00:31:32,720 --> 00:31:34,780
Her eyes look just like my brother's.

468
00:31:36,310 --> 00:31:36,880
Come.

469
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:37,750
Is the baby sleepy?

470
00:31:37,750 --> 00:31:39,180
Here, let me take her.

471
00:31:40,180 --> 00:31:41,580
When Minawar was little,

472
00:31:41,790 --> 00:31:43,770
as soon as she heard my lullabies,

473
00:31:44,030 --> 00:31:45,430
she would sleep soundly.

474
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:47,440
Yes, yes.

475
00:31:47,790 --> 00:31:52,530
♪ Sleep, my baby, sleep, my baby ♪

476
00:31:52,550 --> 00:31:56,070
♪ Sleep, my baby ♪

477
00:31:56,120 --> 00:32:00,580
♪ Sleep, my baby, sleep, my baby ♪

478
00:32:00,740 --> 00:32:05,540
♪ Sleep, my baby, sleep, my baby ♪

479
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:13,570
♪ Sleep, my baby, sleep, my baby ♪

480
00:32:14,150 --> 00:32:21,320
♪ Sleep, my baby, sleep, my baby ♪

481
00:32:23,340 --> 00:32:24,600
Come, eat this.

482
00:32:24,770 --> 00:32:25,180
Gangzi meat.

483
00:32:25,180 --> 00:32:25,600
Eat.

484
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:28,750
Careful, it's hot.

485
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:32,660
We are already way over budget.

486
00:32:33,570 --> 00:32:34,970
Let me do the math for you.

487
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,400
Now the doors, windows, stairs,

488
00:32:37,610 --> 00:32:39,030
and other decorations—

489
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:41,380
Based on their current efficiency,

490
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:43,840
they won't be able
to finish it in half a year.

491
00:32:43,840 --> 00:32:45,010
For the next six months,

492
00:32:45,010 --> 00:32:46,730
we can't just spend money
without making any.

493
00:32:46,730 --> 00:32:47,710
These masters

494
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,970
do work a bit slowly.

495
00:32:49,030 --> 00:32:51,030
But slow work yields fine products.

496
00:32:51,900 --> 00:32:52,570
Think about it,

497
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:53,750
which skilled master

498
00:32:53,750 --> 00:32:54,790
doesn't have a temper,

499
00:32:54,790 --> 00:32:55,680
right?

500
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,480
These pillars are
different from other things.

501
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,940
They will be with this house for decades,

502
00:32:59,940 --> 00:33:01,310
or even centuries.

503
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:03,000
And for our homestay,

504
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:04,350
it's the woodwork that gives
the place its soul.

505
00:33:04,350 --> 00:33:05,160
We must wait

506
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:06,960
for this.

507
00:33:08,030 --> 00:33:08,920
At worst,

508
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,000
when laying the tiles,

509
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,730
we can make up for the lost time.

510
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:14,140
Boss,

511
00:33:15,180 --> 00:33:16,090
we are off work.

512
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:17,980
Okay.

513
00:33:17,980 --> 00:33:19,110
Thanks for your hard work.

514
00:33:19,110 --> 00:33:20,250
See you tomorrow.

515
00:33:20,250 --> 00:33:20,850
Alright.

516
00:33:23,750 --> 00:33:24,940
Where are you going?

517
00:33:24,940 --> 00:33:26,090
Having dinner with my mom.

518
00:33:26,090 --> 00:33:27,090
You can eat this.

519
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,240
Well, you're going

520
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:30,510
to see Auntie?

521
00:33:33,330 --> 00:33:34,930
Auntie, Xia Zi is going home.

522
00:33:35,050 --> 00:33:37,310
You should pack up those things quickly.

523
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:43,720
Who is it?

524
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,270
W-Why are you back?

525
00:33:46,310 --> 00:33:48,840
Don't you want me
to come back and eat with you?

526
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:53,110
I'm super hungry today.

527
00:33:53,110 --> 00:33:54,090
Cook more noodles.

528
00:33:54,090 --> 00:33:55,380
Whatever.

529
00:33:55,380 --> 00:33:56,160
Anything is fine.

530
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:56,920
Okay.

531
00:34:22,230 --> 00:34:24,300
What are you doing in such a hurry?

532
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:27,400
What are you packing?

533
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:32,300
I never had the chance to tell you.

534
00:34:33,030 --> 00:34:34,280
I applied to go to

535
00:34:34,860 --> 00:34:36,460
the Kizil Cave Institute

536
00:34:36,630 --> 00:34:37,730
as a volunteer

537
00:34:37,730 --> 00:34:38,920
to copy murals.

538
00:34:40,190 --> 00:34:41,590
You are leaving Kashgar?

539
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:47,530
Are you selling the wood?

540
00:34:48,980 --> 00:34:51,190
Stop bargaining.
Let's settle it like this.

541
00:34:51,190 --> 00:34:52,590
Load the truck quickly.

542
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,980
We'll still do business in the future.

543
00:34:54,980 --> 00:34:57,040
We are friends. Don't talk like that.

544
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,230
It has to be my mom.

545
00:35:01,230 --> 00:35:03,160
She always manages to surprise me.

546
00:35:03,170 --> 00:35:04,550
She has been

547
00:35:04,550 --> 00:35:06,080
planning it for a long time.

548
00:35:07,190 --> 00:35:09,130
She was worried you'd feel too lonely

549
00:35:09,130 --> 00:35:10,730
being on your own in Kashgar.

550
00:35:12,530 --> 00:35:14,660
You knew about this earlier than I did.

551
00:35:16,670 --> 00:35:18,230
She told me not to tell you.

552
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,340
When I helped her
buy paint last time,

553
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:22,000
she told me to keep it a secret.

554
00:35:22,440 --> 00:35:23,440
I was afraid you'd worry

555
00:35:23,440 --> 00:35:24,880
about her heart

556
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:25,880
and health.

557
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:27,880
I was just thinking of you.

558
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:32,940
Tell me,

559
00:35:33,530 --> 00:35:35,650
when did we start

560
00:35:37,050 --> 00:35:39,230
looking out for each other like this?

561
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,860
You know, for the neck

562
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,260
of the instruments we make,

563
00:35:51,260 --> 00:35:53,110
we use "male" wood.

564
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:55,320
"Male," as in male and female.

565
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:56,210
They are divided into male and female?

566
00:35:56,210 --> 00:35:57,960
Yes, male.

567
00:35:58,190 --> 00:35:59,280
Look, hold it like this.

568
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:00,360
If you want to grab it, do this.

569
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:01,110
Like this.

570
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,400
Because the male one is harder,

571
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:04,440
and the female one is softer.

572
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:06,170
They match better for the tone.

573
00:36:06,590 --> 00:36:09,050
I feel that making earthenware is easier.

574
00:36:09,050 --> 00:36:10,590
The clay is soft,

575
00:36:10,590 --> 00:36:11,670
unlike this wood—

576
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:14,170
It's rock hard.

577
00:36:22,460 --> 00:36:23,480
I give up.

578
00:36:23,670 --> 00:36:24,920
I'm telling you,

579
00:36:25,150 --> 00:36:26,400
it's these woods

580
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,900
that make the most beautiful sounds.

581
00:36:29,510 --> 00:36:31,770
Then why do you like making instruments?

582
00:36:32,510 --> 00:36:35,710
My family has been making instruments
for 7 generations.

583
00:36:35,880 --> 00:36:37,960
So I was born to make instruments.

584
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:39,980
When I was young,

585
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,670
I was actually very envious

586
00:36:41,670 --> 00:36:44,530
of kids who could play football
right after school.

587
00:36:44,940 --> 00:36:45,960
Until I was...

588
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:47,110
thir...

589
00:36:47,110 --> 00:36:47,380
right,

590
00:36:47,380 --> 00:36:48,550
thirteen years old.

591
00:36:49,070 --> 00:36:50,960
I made my first instrument.

592
00:36:51,710 --> 00:36:54,110
When I plucked the string like this

593
00:36:54,670 --> 00:36:56,110
and heard it hum,

594
00:36:57,920 --> 00:37:00,550
I felt like the whole world
had settled down.

595
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:02,710
I understand that feeling.

596
00:37:02,710 --> 00:37:03,550
It's like

597
00:37:03,780 --> 00:37:05,300
suddenly your eyes

598
00:37:05,300 --> 00:37:06,670
really opened,

599
00:37:06,670 --> 00:37:08,840
and the whole world became bright.

600
00:37:08,840 --> 00:37:09,960
It's like

601
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:10,940
I know

602
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,710
where I can go,

603
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:14,320
and where I will go.

604
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:16,860
Every time I make earthenware,

605
00:37:17,190 --> 00:37:18,880
I feel like

606
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:20,190
I'm no longer Laili.

607
00:37:20,190 --> 00:37:21,840
I become a different Laili.

608
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:23,710
I became

609
00:37:23,710 --> 00:37:24,920
stronger,

610
00:37:24,920 --> 00:37:26,130
calmer,

611
00:37:26,130 --> 00:37:27,480
undisturbed,

612
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,710
and more focused.

613
00:37:30,460 --> 00:37:31,920
Then you should be bolder,

614
00:37:32,210 --> 00:37:34,140
and go create work that's your own.

615
00:37:35,610 --> 00:37:36,860
Do you remember the song

616
00:37:36,860 --> 00:37:38,460
I sang in the alley last time?

617
00:37:38,840 --> 00:37:39,820
I've finished writing it.

618
00:37:39,820 --> 00:37:40,860
Finished?

619
00:38:02,580 --> 00:38:07,140
♪ We are lonely souls ♪

620
00:38:09,420 --> 00:38:14,590
♪ Drifting in and out of the crowds ♪

621
00:38:15,850 --> 00:38:21,520
♪ Confining dusk within the dawn ♪

622
00:38:22,590 --> 00:38:27,270
♪ Waiting aimlessly
for the traffic lights ♪

623
00:38:29,180 --> 00:38:34,520
♪ Suddenly, I never ask again ♪

624
00:38:35,620 --> 00:38:41,030
♪ About the lingering warmth upon waking ♪

625
00:38:41,870 --> 00:38:48,020
♪ This unexpected sincerity ♪

626
00:38:44,980 --> 00:38:46,580
Aren't we just good friends?

627
00:38:49,060 --> 00:38:54,270
♪ Makes each of our lives complete ♪

628
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:53,130
Ordinary friends.

629
00:38:55,130 --> 00:39:02,020
♪ I can't quite describe it ♪

630
00:38:59,540 --> 00:39:01,000
Long live our friendship.

631
00:39:02,290 --> 00:39:05,470
♪ A sudden, unexpected surprise ♪

632
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:08,520
♪ Don't go away too fast ♪

633
00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:15,260
♪ It truly exists ♪

634
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:18,910
♪ Thank you for your generosity ♪

635
00:39:18,930 --> 00:39:23,640
♪ For making me believe in love ♪

636
00:39:32,180 --> 00:39:37,510
♪ We are the lucky ones ♪

637
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,880
I think this material is really good.

638
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,610
It's perfect for our homestay.

639
00:39:38,420 --> 00:39:39,360
Take a look.

640
00:39:38,940 --> 00:39:44,450
♪ Mixed with complicated feelings
at times ♪

641
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:44,550
This one?

642
00:39:45,230 --> 00:39:45,960
I think it's okay.

643
00:39:45,960 --> 00:39:47,510
We can put it at the doorplate.

644
00:39:46,070 --> 00:39:51,760
♪ The mornings we wake up together ♪

645
00:39:47,510 --> 00:39:49,640
I feel like this one's not quite right.

646
00:39:50,530 --> 00:39:52,170
If you think it's not right,
why call me over?

647
00:39:52,170 --> 00:39:58,070
♪ Often leave me staring
at you in a daze ♪

648
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,000
You take a look for yourself.

649
00:39:58,370 --> 00:40:05,570
♪ I can't quite describe it ♪

650
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:00,710
Xia Zi,

651
00:40:00,710 --> 00:40:03,400
what do you think of Zhou?

652
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,000
Mom, it's been ages
since I've even been in a relationship.

653
00:40:05,860 --> 00:40:09,200
♪ A sudden, unexpected surprise ♪

654
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:08,940
I haven't even figured out
my own life yet.

655
00:40:08,940 --> 00:40:11,070
How can I start with someone else?

656
00:40:09,230 --> 00:40:11,690
♪ Don't go away too fast ♪

657
00:40:11,760 --> 00:40:18,730
♪ It truly exists ♪

658
00:40:14,590 --> 00:40:16,170
Does this fig

659
00:40:17,050 --> 00:40:18,960
have a heart

660
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:21,890
♪ Thank you for your generosity ♪

661
00:40:19,300 --> 00:40:21,030
or not?

662
00:40:22,060 --> 00:40:27,740
♪ For making me believe in love ♪

663
00:40:43,860 --> 00:40:47,090
An extra 320,000.

664
00:40:59,340 --> 00:41:00,340
I'll...

665
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,100
go back to my hometown.

666
00:41:05,840 --> 00:41:06,960
For how long?

667
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,000
I don't know, either.

668
00:41:14,610 --> 00:41:16,140
I need to raise money first.

669
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:18,730
Only after tearing the place down

670
00:41:18,730 --> 00:41:21,990
did we realize the drainage
and gas lines all need redoing—

671
00:41:22,030 --> 00:41:23,110
oh, and...

672
00:41:24,150 --> 00:41:26,350
the water and electrical systems, too.

673
00:41:26,610 --> 00:41:27,950
I'll go back first.

674
00:41:28,340 --> 00:41:30,380
We'll pause the construction here for now.

675
00:41:30,380 --> 00:41:32,490
I'll rush back as soon as I get the money.

676
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:34,930
Please take good care of my sapling.

677
00:41:35,610 --> 00:41:37,130
Oh, don't worry.

678
00:41:37,130 --> 00:41:39,510
I'll water it when I water mine.

679
00:41:41,370 --> 00:41:43,170
What's there to worry about?

680
00:41:52,830 --> 00:41:55,250
Congratulations on your
honorable retirement, Dr. Chang.

681
00:41:55,250 --> 00:41:56,450
Thank you, Director.

682
00:42:31,360 --> 00:42:32,250
Thank you.

683
00:42:32,670 --> 00:42:33,970
Thank you, everyone.

684
00:42:35,380 --> 00:42:36,820
Thank you, everyone.

685
00:42:39,050 --> 00:42:40,010
Thank you.

686
00:42:40,860 --> 00:42:41,880
Dr. Chang.

687
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:45,030
Congratulations on your retirement.

688
00:42:52,420 --> 00:42:53,380
May you

689
00:42:53,820 --> 00:42:54,950
unburden yourself,

690
00:42:55,610 --> 00:42:57,340
start your new chapter afresh,

691
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,340
and find your inner path.
